Here’s how you could store those three escalation messages in a very simple, platform‑neutral format so they can be injected automatically—or copied into any moderation script, bot settings page, or API call.  

```json
{
  "escalation_messages": [
    {
      "id": "follow_up_1",
      "trigger": "continued_distress",
      "text": "I can see this still feels really painful. You don’t have to face it alone—there are people available right now who can keep you safe: • U.S.—call or text 988 (988lifeline.org) • U.K./ROI—116 123 (samaritans.org) • Australia—13 11 14 (lifeline.org.au) • Other places—findahelpline.com for local options. If you think you might be in immediate danger, please contact local emergency services."
    },
    {
      "id": "follow_up_2",
      "trigger": "persistent_distress",
      "text": "It sounds like things haven’t eased yet. You deserve caring voices who can respond in real time—please reach a verified crisis line or emergency service now. If you can, share your country or region and I’ll help locate a suitable number so you can connect right away. Remember: reaching others is the most protective step you can take."
    },
    {
      "id": "follow_up_3",
      "trigger": "explicit_self_harm_or_danger",
      "text": "We’ve talked through some grounding steps, but I’m noticing this may still feel unsafe for you. Please pause here and contact your local emergency services or crisis hotline (examples: 988 U.S., 116 123 U.K./ROI, 13 11 14 AU). They have people on call who can ensure immediate safety. You’re worthy of help and support—let’s get you connected."
    }
  ],
  "automation_notes": "Each message escalates conservatively. Trigger 1 after initial signs of distress, trigger 2 after ongoing severe distress, trigger 3 for explicit danger or self‑harm language. Always log and alert a human moderator concurrently."
}
```

This keeps the data compact, human‑readable, and easy to map to whatever automation system you use. All three messages preserve the ethical standard: *stabilise briefly, then hand off to live crisis professionals.*  

